      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While wind and solar are essential, they cannot replace nuclear energy alone because they are intermittent and require massive storage solutions that are currently economically unfeasible. Without nuclear's ability to provide reliable baseload power, the grid would collapse during peak demand, making net zero impossible to achieve.\n\nTherefore, nuclear is not just a necessity but a critical component of any realistic plan to hit net zero by 2050.",
      "source": "target",
